summary: Extremely motivated and dependable Laborer with years of extensive experience in general maintenance and construction tasks ranging from demolitions to site clearing and debris removal. Proven physical stamina with a demonstrated ability to work without supervision. A fun and friendly individual who enjoy working collaboratively.

experience.title: Mover
experience.description: Moved materials from warehouse to businesses or residential areas throughout Maryland and D.C.; loaded/unloaded trucks, vans, or automobiles; operated forklifts and hand trucks; installed protective bracing, padding and strapping to prevent shifting and damage; performed pre-trip checks and basic vehicle maintenance; maintained records of materials during transfers; adhered to OSHA standards; lifted 80-100 pounds as part of daily duties.

experience.title: Warehouse Selector / Driver
experience.description: Selected, loaded, moved, and unloaded wine supplies; operated forklift; maintained inventory; picked and filled orders; replenished supplies; coordinated with transporters and suppliers for dispatch and procurement; tracked delivery information, truck mileage, and fuel usage; transported product to liquor stores and vintners; ensured freshness and proper storage; performed warehouse maintenance.

experience.title: Laborer
experience.description: Lifted heavy loads up to 70 lbs; dug pits, trenches, and foundations; operated heavy machinery; identified utility lines; performed setup and cleanup; directed traffic for safety; provided labor support for specialty crews; maintained construction equipment; assisted in building structures for residential, commercial, and construction sites; participated in demolitions; worked underground; removed trees and debris; serviced pumps, compressors, generators, tractors, and trailers; mixed concrete.

experience.title: Fitness and Aqua Aerobics Instructor
experience.description: Explain and enforce safety rules and regulations governing sports and recreational activities; offer alternatives during classes to accommodate different fitness levels; teach breathing techniques; instruct participants in maintaining exertion levels to maximize benefits; teach and demonstrate use of gym equipment; evaluate individuals' abilities and develop suitable training programs; plan physical education programs to promote development of physical attributes and social skills.
